Patient: What kind of exercise can I do for my heart condition?
Healthcare Educator: Gentle activities like walking or swimming can help strengthen your heart safely. 

Patient: I live in an unsafe neighborhood, can I exercise indoors?
Healthcare Educator: Yes, you can. There are many indoor exercises like yoga or using a stationary bike.

Patient: I don't have money for gym or equipment, any other suggestions?
Healthcare Educator: Household chores like cleaning, gardening, or dancing to music can also be good exercise. 

Patient: How long should I exercise each day?
Healthcare Educator: Start with 10 minutes daily, then slowly increase to 30 minutes at least five days a week.

Patient: What if I get tired quickly?
Healthcare Educator: It's okay to take breaks. Listen to your body and don't overdo it. Exercise should not cause pain.